ys#ref30166"><em>Madness of Heracles</em></a></li></ul><ul class="list-unstyled" data-level="h2"><li data-target="#ref30167"><a href="https://www.britannica.com/biography/Euripides/The-plays#ref30167"><em>Trojan Women</em></a></li></ul><ul class="list-unstyled" data-level="h2"><li data-target="#ref30168"><a href="https://www.britannica.com/biography/Euripides/Ion"><em>Ion</em></a></li></ul><ul class="list-unstyled" data-level="h2"><li data-target="#ref30169"><a href="https://www.britannica.com/biography/Euripides/Ion#ref30169"><em>Iphigenia Among the Taurians</em></a></li></ul><ul class="list-unstyled" data-level="h2"><li data-target="#ref30170"><a href="https://www.britannica.com/biography/Euripides/Ion#ref30170"><em>Helen</em></a></li></ul><ul class="list-unstyled" data-level="h2"><li data-target="#ref30171"><a href="https://www.britannica.com/biography/Euripides/Ion#ref30171"><em>Phoenician Women</em></a></li></ul><ul class="list-unstyled" data-level="h2"><li data-target="#ref30172"><a href="https://www.britannica.com/biography/Euripides/Ion#ref30172"><em>Orestes</em></a></li></ul><ul class="list-unstyled" data-level="h2"><li data-target="#ref30173"><a href="https://www.britannica.com/biography/Euripides/Ion#ref30173"><em>Iphigenia at Aulis</em></a></li></ul><ul class="list-unstyled" data-level="h2"><li data-target="#ref30174"><a href="https://www.britannica.com/biography/Euripides/Ion#ref30174"><em>Bacchants</em></a></li></ul><ul class="list-unstyled" data-level="h2"><li data-target="#ref30175"><a href="https://www.britannica.com/biography/Euripides/Ion#ref30175"><em>Cyclops</em></a></li></ul></li></ul></div>
